var book = {
	"name": "Nehemiah",
	"numChapters": 13,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The words of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12298A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12298A\"></sup>Nehemiah the son of Hacaliah.Now it happened in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12298B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12298B\"></sup>the month Chislev, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12298C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12298C\"></sup><i>in</i> the twentieth year, while I was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12298D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12298D\"></sup>Susa the capitol,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12299E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12299E\"></sup>Hanani, one of my brothers, and some men from Judah came; and I asked them concerning the Jews who had escaped <i>and</i> had survived the captivity, and about Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to me, “The remnant there in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12300F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12300F\"></sup>province who survived the captivity are in great distress and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12300G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12300G\"></sup>reproach, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12300H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12300H\"></sup>the wall of Jerusalem is broken down and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12300I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12300I\"></sup>its gates are burned with fire.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When I heard these words, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12301J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12301J\"></sup>I sat down and wept and mourned for days; and I was fasting and praying before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12301K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12301K\"></sup>the God of heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I said, “I beseech You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12302L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12302L\"></sup>the great and awesome God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12302M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12302M\"></sup>who preserves the covenant and lovingkindness for those who love Him and keep His commandments,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12303N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12303N\"></sup>let Your ear now be attentive and Your eyes open to hear the prayer of Your servant which I am praying before You now, day and night, on behalf of the sons of Israel Your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12303O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12303O\"></sup>confessing the sins of the sons of Israel which we have sinned against You; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12303P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12303P\"></sup>I and my father’s house have sinned.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12304Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12304Q\"></sup>We have acted very corruptly against You and have not kept the commandments, nor the statutes, nor the ordinances <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12304R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12304R\"></sup>which You commanded Your servant Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Remember the word which You commanded Your servant Moses, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12305S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12305S\"></sup>If you are unfaithful I will scatter you among the peoples;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12306T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12306T\"></sup>but <i>if</i> you return to Me and keep My commandments and do them, though those of you who have been scattered were in the most remote part of the heavens, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12306U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12306U\"></sup>will gather them from there and will bring them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12306V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12306V\"></sup>to the place where I have chosen to cause My name to dwell.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12307W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12307W\"></sup>They are Your servants and Your people whom You redeemed by Your great power and by Your strong hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>O Lord, I beseech You, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12308X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12308X\"></sup>may Your ear be attentive to the prayer of Your servant and the prayer of Your servants who delight to revere Your name, and make Your servant successful today and grant him compassion before this man.”Now I was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12308Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12308Y\"></sup>cupbearer to the king."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>And it came about in the month Nisan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12309A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12309A\"></sup>in the twentieth year of King <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12309B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12309B\"></sup>Artaxerxes, that wine <i>was</i> before him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12309C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12309C\"></sup>I took up the wine and gave it to the king. Now I had not been sad in his presence.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king said to me, “Why is your face sad though you are not sick? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12310D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12310D\"></sup>This is nothing but sadness of heart.” Then I was very much afraid.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12311E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12311E\"></sup>Let the king live forever. Why should my face not be sad <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12311F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12311F\"></sup>when the city, the place of my fathers’ tombs, lies desolate and its gates have been consumed by fire?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to me, “What would you request?” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12312G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12312G\"></sup>So I prayed to the God of heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I said to the king, “If it please the king, and if your servant has found favor before you, send me to Judah, to the city of my fathers’ tombs, that I may rebuild it.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the king said to me, the queen sitting beside him, “How long will your journey be, and when will you return?” So it pleased the king to send me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12314H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12314H\"></sup>I gave him a definite time.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And I said to the king, “If it please the king, let letters be given me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12315I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12315I\"></sup>for the governors <i>of the provinces</i> beyond the River, that they may allow me to pass through until I come to Judah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and a letter to Asaph the keeper of the king’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12316J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12316J\"></sup>forest, that he may give me timber to make beams for the gates of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12316K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12316K\"></sup>the fortress which is by the temple, for the wall of the city and for the house to which I will go.” And the king granted <i>them</i> to me because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12316L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12316L\"></sup>the good hand of my God <i>was</i> on me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12317M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12317M\"></sup>the governors <i>of the provinces</i> beyond the River and gave them the king’s letters. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12317N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12317N\"></sup>the king had sent with me officers of the army and horsemen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12318O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12318O\"></sup>Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official heard <i>about it</i>, it was very displeasing to them that someone had come to seek the welfare of the sons of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12319P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12319P\"></sup>came to Jerusalem and was there three days.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And I arose in the night, I and a few men with me. I did not tell anyone what my God was putting into my mind to do for Jerusalem and there was no animal with me except the animal on which I was riding.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So I went out at night by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12321Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12321Q\"></sup>the Valley Gate in the direction of the Dragon’s Well and <i>on</i> to the Refuse Gate, inspecting the walls of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12321R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12321R\"></sup>which were broken down and its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12321S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12321S\"></sup>gates which were consumed by fire.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then I passed on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12322T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12322T\"></sup>the Fountain Gate and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12322U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12322U\"></sup>the King’s Pool, but there was no place for my mount to pass.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So I went up at night by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12323V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12323V\"></sup>ravine and inspected the wall. Then I entered the Valley Gate again and returned.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The officials did not know where I had gone or what I had done; nor had I as yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials or the rest who did the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then I said to them, “You see the bad situation we are in, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12325W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12325W\"></sup>Jerusalem is desolate and its gates burned by fire. Come, let us rebuild the wall of Jerusalem so that we will no longer be a reproach.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I told them how the hand of my God had been favorable to me and also about the king’s words which he had spoken to me. Then they said, “Let us arise and build.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12326X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12326X\"></sup>So they put their hands to the good <i>work</i>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12327Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12327Y\"></sup>Geshem the Arab heard <i>it</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12327Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12327Z\"></sup>they mocked us and despised us and said, “What is this thing you are doing? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12327AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12327AA\"></sup>Are you rebelling against the king?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So I answered them and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12328AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12328AB\"></sup>The God of heaven will give us success; therefore we His servants will arise and build, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12328AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12328AC\"></sup>but you have no portion, right or memorial in Jerusalem.”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12329A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12329A\"></sup>Eliashib the high priest arose with his brothers the priests and built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12329B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12329B\"></sup>the Sheep Gate; they consecrated it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12329C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12329C\"></sup>hung its doors. They consecrated the wall to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12329D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12329D\"></sup>the Tower of the Hundred <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12329E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12329E\"></sup>the Tower of Hananel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Next to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12330F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12330F\"></sup>the men of Jericho built, and next to them Zaccur the son of Imri built.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now the sons of Hassenaah built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12331G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12331G\"></sup>the Fish Gate; they laid its beams and hung its doors with its bolts and bars.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Next to them Meremoth the son of Uriah the son of Hakkoz made repairs. And next to him Meshullam the son of Berechiah the son of Meshezabel made repairs. And next to him Zadok the son of Baana <i>also</i> made repairs.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, next to him the Tekoites made repairs, but their nobles did not support the work of their masters.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Joiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah repaired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12334H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12334H\"></sup>the Old Gate; they laid its beams and hung its doors with its bolts and its bars.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Next to them Melatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite, the men of Gibeon and of Mizpah, also made repairs for the official seat of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12335I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12335I\"></sup>governor <i>of the province</i> beyond the River.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Next to him Uzziel the son of Harhaiah of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12336J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12336J\"></sup>goldsmiths made repairs. And next to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, made repairs, and they restored Jerusalem as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12336K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12336K\"></sup>the Broad Wall.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12337L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12337L\"></sup>the official of half the district of Jerusalem, made repairs.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph made repairs opposite his house. And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabneiah made repairs.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Malchijah the son of Harim and Hasshub the son of Pahath-moab repaired another section and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12339M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12339M\"></sup>the Tower of Furnaces.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Next to him Shallum the son of Hallohesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12340N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12340N\"></sup>the official of half the district of Jerusalem, made repairs, he and his daughters.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12341O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12341O\"></sup>the Valley Gate. They built it and hung its doors with its bolts and its bars, and a thousand cubits of the wall to the Refuse Gate.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Malchijah the son of Rechab, the official of the district of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12342P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12342P\"></sup>Beth-haccherem repaired the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12342Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12342Q\"></sup>Refuse Gate. He built it and hung its doors with its bolts and its bars.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Shallum the son of Col-hozeh, the official of the district of Mizpah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12343R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12343R\"></sup>repaired the Fountain Gate. He built it, covered it and hung its doors with its bolts and its bars, and the wall of the Pool of Shelah at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12343S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12343S\"></sup>the king’s garden as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12343T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12343T\"></sup>the steps that descend from the city of David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12344U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12344U\"></sup>official of half the district of Beth-zur, made repairs as far as <i>a point</i> opposite the tombs of David, and as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12344V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12344V\"></sup>the artificial pool and the house of the mighty men.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After him the Levites carried out repairs <i>under</i> Rehum the son of Bani. Next to him Hashabiah, the official of half the district of Keilah, carried out repairs for his district.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After him their brothers carried out repairs <i>under</i> Bavvai the son of Henadad, official of <i>the other</i> half of the district of Keilah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12347W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12347W\"></sup>the official of Mizpah, repaired another section in front of the ascent of the armory <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12347X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12347X\"></sup>at the Angle.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After him Baruch the son of Zabbai zealously repaired another section, from the Angle to the doorway of the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12348Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12348Y\"></sup>Eliashib the high priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After him Meremoth the son of Uriah the son of Hakkoz repaired another section, from the doorway of Eliashib’s house even as far as the end of his house.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After him the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12350Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12350Z\"></sup>the men of the valley, carried out repairs.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After them Benjamin and Hasshub carried out repairs in front of their house. After them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, son of Ananiah, carried out repairs beside his house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section, from the house of Azariah as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12352AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12352AA\"></sup>the Angle and as far as the corner.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Palal the son of Uzai <i>made repairs</i> in front of the Angle and the tower projecting from the upper house of the king, which is by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12353AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12353AB\"></sup>the court of the guard. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh <i>made repairs</i>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12354AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12354AC\"></sup>The temple servants living in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12354AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12354AD\"></sup>Ophel <i>made repairs</i> as far as the front of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12354AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12354AE\"></sup>the Water Gate toward the east and the projecting tower.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>After them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12355AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12355AF\"></sup>the Tekoites repaired another section in front of the great projecting tower and as far as the wall of Ophel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12356AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12356AG\"></sup>the Horse Gate the priests carried out repairs, each in front of his house.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>After them Zadok the son of Immer carried out repairs in front of his house. And after him Shemaiah the son of Shecaniah, the keeper of the East Gate, carried out repairs.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah, and Hanun the sixth son of Zalaph, repaired another section. After him Meshullam the son of Berechiah carried out repairs in front of his own quarters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After him Malchijah, one of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12359AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12359AH\"></sup>the goldsmiths, carried out repairs as far as the house of the temple servants and of the merchants, in front of the Inspection Gate and as far as the upper room of the corner.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Between the upper room of the corner and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12360AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12360AI\"></sup>the Sheep Gate the goldsmiths and the merchants carried out repairs."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now it came about that when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12361A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12361A\"></sup>Sanballat heard that we were rebuilding the wall, he became furious and very angry and mocked the Jews.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He spoke in the presence of his brothers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12362B\"></sup>the wealthy <i>men</i> of Samaria and said, “What are these feeble Jews doing? Are they going to restore <i>it</i> for themselves? Can they offer sacrifices? Can they finish in a day? Can they revive the stones from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12362C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12362C\"></sup>dusty rubble even the burned ones?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Tobiah the Ammonite <i>was</i> near him and he said, “Even what they are building—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12363D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12363D\"></sup>if a fox should jump on <i>it</i>, he would break their stone wall down!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12364E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12364E\"></sup>Hear, O our God, how we are despised! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12364F\"></sup>Return their reproach on their own heads and give them up for plunder in a land of captivity.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12365G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12365G\"></sup>forgive their iniquity and let not their sin be blotted out before You, for they have demoralized the builders.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So we built the wall and the whole wall was joined together to half its <i>height</i>, for the people had a mind to work.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now when Sanballat, Tobiah, the Arabs, the Ammonites and the Ashdodites heard that the repair of the walls of Jerusalem went on, <i>and</i> that the breaches began to be closed, they were very angry.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All of them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12368H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12368H\"></sup>conspired together to come <i>and</i> fight against Jerusalem and to cause a disturbance in it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But we prayed to our God, and because of them we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12369I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12369I\"></sup>set up a guard against them day and night.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Thus in Judah it was said,“The strength of the burden bearers is failing,Yet there is much rubbish;And we ourselves are unableTo rebuild the wall.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Our enemies said, “They will not know or see until we come among them, kill them and put a stop to the work.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the Jews who lived near them came and told us ten times, “They will come up against us from every place where you may turn,”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>then I stationed <i>men</i> in the lowest parts of the space behind the wall, the exposed places, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12373J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12373J\"></sup>stationed the people in families with their swords, spears and bows.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When I saw <i>their fear</i>, I rose and spoke to the nobles, the officials and the rest of the people: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12374K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12374K\"></sup>Do not be afraid of them; remember the Lord who is great and awesome, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12374L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12374L\"></sup>fight for your brothers, your sons, your daughters, your wives and your houses.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When our enemies heard that it was known to us, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12375M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12375M\"></sup>God had frustrated their plan, then all of us returned to the wall, each one to his work.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>From that day on, half of my servants carried on the work while half of them held the spears, the shields, the bows and the breastplates; and the captains <i>were</i> behind the whole house of Judah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Those who were rebuilding the wall and those who carried burdens took <i>their</i> load with one hand doing the work and the other holding a weapon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As for the builders, each <i>wore</i> his sword girded at his side as he built, while the trumpeter <i>stood</i> near me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I said to the nobles, the officials and the rest of the people, “The work is great and extensive, and we are separated on the wall far from one another.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>At whatever place you hear the sound of the trumpet, rally to us there. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12380N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12380N\"></sup>Our God will fight for us.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So we carried on the work with half of them holding spears from dawn until the stars appeared.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>At that time I also said to the people, “Let each man with his servant spend the night within Jerusalem so that they may be a guard for us by night and a laborer by day.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So neither I, my brothers, my servants, nor the men of the guard who followed me, none of us removed our clothes, each <i>took</i> his weapon <i>even to</i> the water."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12384A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12384A\"></sup>there was a great outcry of the people and of their wives against their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12384B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12384B\"></sup>Jewish brothers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For there were those who said, “We, our sons and our daughters are many; therefore let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12385C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12385C\"></sup>get grain that we may eat and live.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There were others who said, “We are mortgaging our fields, our vineyards and our houses that we might get grain because of the famine.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Also there were those who said, “We have borrowed money <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12387D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12387D\"></sup>for the king’s tax <i>on</i> our fields and our vineyards.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12388E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12388E\"></sup>our flesh is like the flesh of our brothers, our children like their children. Yet behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12388F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12388F\"></sup>we are forcing our sons and our daughters to be slaves, and some of our daughters are forced into bondage <i>already</i>, and we are helpless because our fields and vineyards belong to others.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then I was very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12389G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12389G\"></sup>angry when I had heard their outcry and these words.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I consulted with myself and contended with the nobles and the rulers and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12390H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12390H\"></sup>You are exacting usury, each from his brother!” Therefore, I held a great assembly against them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I said to them, “We according to our ability <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12391I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12391I\"></sup>have redeemed our Jewish brothers who were sold to the nations; now would you even sell your brothers that they may be sold to us?” Then they were silent and could not find a word <i>to say</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Again I said, “The thing which you are doing is not good; should you not walk in the fear of our God because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12392J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12392J\"></sup>the reproach of the nations, our enemies?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And likewise I, my brothers and my servants are lending them money and grain. Please, let us leave off this usury.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Please, give back to them this very day their fields, their vineyards, their olive groves and their houses, also the hundredth <i>part</i> of the money and of the grain, the new wine and the oil that you are exacting from them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they said, “We <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12395K\"></sup>will give <i>it</i> back and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12395L\"></sup>will require nothing from them; we will do exactly as you say.” So I called the priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12395M\"></sup>took an oath from them that they would do according to this promise.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12396N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12396N\"></sup>also shook out the front of my garment and said, “Thus may God shake out every man from his house and from his possessions who does not fulfill this promise; even thus may he be shaken out and emptied.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12396O\"></sup>all the assembly said, “Amen!” And they praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then the people did according to this promise.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, from the day that I was appointed to be their governor in the land of Judah, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12397P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12397P\"></sup>the twentieth year to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12397Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12397Q\"></sup>thirty-second year of King Artaxerxes, <i>for</i> twelve years, neither I nor my kinsmen have eaten the governor’s food <i>allowance</i>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the former governors who were before me laid burdens on the people and took from them bread and wine besides forty shekels of silver; even their servants domineered the people. But I did not do so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12398R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12398R\"></sup>because of the fear of God.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I also applied myself to the work on this wall; we did not buy any land, and all my servants were gathered there for the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12400S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12400S\"></sup><i>there were</i> at my table one hundred and fifty Jews and officials, besides those who came to us from the nations that were around us.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12401T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12401T\"></sup>that which was prepared for each day was one ox <i>and</i> six choice sheep, also birds were prepared for me; and once in ten days all sorts of wine <i>were furnished</i> in abundance. Yet for all this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12401U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12401U\"></sup>I did not demand the governor’s food <i>allowance</i>, because the servitude was heavy on this people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12402V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12402V\"></sup>Remember me, O my God, for good, <i>according to</i> all that I have done for this people."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now when it was reported to Sanballat, Tobiah, to Geshem the Arab and to the rest of our enemies that I had rebuilt the wall, and <i>that</i> no breach remained in it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12403A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12403A\"></sup>although at that time I had not set up the doors in the gates,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then Sanballat and Geshem sent <i>a message</i> to me, saying, “Come, let us meet together at Chephirim in the plain of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12404B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12404B\"></sup>Ono.” But they were planning to harm me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So I sent messengers to them, saying, “I am doing a great work and I cannot come down. Why should the work stop while I leave it and come down to you?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They sent <i>messages</i> to me four times in this manner, and I answered them in the same way.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Sanballat sent his servant to me in the same manner a fifth time with an open letter in his hand.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In it was written, “It is reported among the nations, and Gashmu says, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12408C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12408C\"></sup>you and the Jews are planning to rebel; therefore you are rebuilding the wall. And you are to be their king, according to these reports.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You have also appointed prophets to proclaim in Jerusalem concerning you, ‘A king is in Judah!’ And now it will be reported to the king according to these reports. So come now, let us take counsel together.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then I sent <i>a message</i> to him saying, “Such things as you are saying have not been done, but you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12410D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12410D\"></sup>inventing them in your own mind.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For all of them were <i>trying</i> to frighten us, thinking, “They will become discouraged with the work and it will not be done.” But now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12411E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12411E\"></sup><i>O God</i>, strengthen my hands.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When I entered the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, son of Mehetabel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12412F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12412F\"></sup>who was confined at home, he said, “Let us meet together in the house of God, within the temple, and let us close the doors of the temple, for they are coming to kill you, and they are coming to kill you at night.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But I said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12413G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12413G\"></sup>Should a man like me flee? And could one such as I go into the temple to save his life? I will not go in.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then I perceived that surely God had not sent him, but he uttered <i>his</i> prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He was hired for this reason, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12415H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12415H\"></sup>that I might become frightened and act accordingly and sin, so that they might have an evil report in order that they could reproach me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12416I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12416I\"></sup>Remember, O my God, Tobiah and Sanballat according to these works of theirs, and also Noadiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12416J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12416J\"></sup>the prophetess and the rest of the prophets who were <i>trying</i> to frighten me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12417K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12417K\"></sup>the wall was completed on the twenty-fifth of <i>the month</i> Elul, in fifty-two days.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12418L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12418L\"></sup>When all our enemies heard <i>of it</i>, and all the nations surrounding us saw <i>it</i>, they lost their confidence; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12418M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12418M\"></sup>they recognized that this work had been accomplished with the help of our God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Also in those days many letters went from the nobles of Judah to Tobiah, and Tobiah’s <i>letters</i> came to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For many in Judah were bound by oath to him because he was the son-in-law of Shecaniah the son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter of Meshullam the son of Berechiah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moreover, they were speaking about his good deeds in my presence and reported my words to him. Then Tobiah sent letters to frighten me."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12422A\"></sup>the wall was rebuilt and I had set up the doors, and the gatekeepers and the singers and the Levites were appointed,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then I put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12423B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12423B\"></sup>Hanani my brother, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12423C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12423C\"></sup>Hananiah the commander of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12423D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12423D\"></sup>the fortress, in charge of Jerusalem, for he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12423E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12423E\"></sup>a faithful man and feared God more than many.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then I said to them, “Do not let the gates of Jerusalem be opened until the sun is hot, and while they are standing <i>guard</i>, let them shut and bolt the doors. Also appoint guards from the inhabitants of Jerusalem, each at his post, and each in front of his own house.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now the city was large and spacious, but the people in it were few and the houses were not built.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12426F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12426F\"></sup>Then my God put it into my heart to assemble the nobles, the officials and the people to be enrolled by genealogies. Then I found the book of the genealogy of those who came up first in which I found the following record:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12427G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12427G\"></sup>These are the people of the province who came up from the captivity of the exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his city,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>who came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah.The number of men of the people of Israel:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the sons of Parosh, 2,172;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>the sons of Shephatiah, 372;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the sons of Arah, 652;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the sons of Pahath-moab of the sons of Jeshua and Joab, 2,818;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the sons of Elam, 1,254;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the sons of Zattu, 845;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the sons of Zaccai, 760;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the sons of Binnui, 648;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the sons of Bebai, 628;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the sons of Azgad, 2,322;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the sons of Adonikam, 667;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the sons of Bigvai, 2,067;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the sons of Adin, 655;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the sons of Ater, of Hezekiah, 98;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the sons of Hashum, 328;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>the sons of Bezai, 324;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the sons of Hariph, 112;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the sons of Gibeon, 95;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the men of Bethlehem and Netophah, 188;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the men of Anathoth, 128;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>the men of Beth-azmaveth, 42;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>the men of Kiriath-jearim, Chephirah and Beeroth, 743;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the men of Ramah and Geba, 621;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the men of Michmas, 122;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>the men of Bethel and Ai, 123;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>the men of the other Nebo, 52;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the sons of the other Elam, 1,254;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the sons of Harim, 320;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the men of Jericho, 345;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the sons of Lod, Hadid and Ono, 721;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the sons of Senaah, 3,930.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The priests: the sons of Jedaiah of the house of Jeshua, 973;",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>the sons of Immer, 1,052;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the sons of Pashhur, 1,247;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>the sons of Harim, 1,017.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, of Kadmiel, of the sons of Hodevah, 74.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The singers: the sons of Asaph, 148.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, the sons of Shobai, 138.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The temple servants: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>the sons of Keros, the sons of Sia, the sons of Padon,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>the sons of Lebana, the sons of Hagaba, the sons of Shalmai,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>the sons of Hanan, the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>the sons of Reaiah, the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>the sons of Gazzam, the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>the sons of Besai, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephushesim,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>the sons of Bazlith, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Temah,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>the sons of Neziah, the sons of Hatipha.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>The sons of Solomon’s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of Perida,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim, the sons of Amon.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>All the temple servants and the sons of Solomon’s servants <i>were</i> 392.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>These <i>were</i> they who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addon and Immer; but they could not show their fathers’ houses or their descendants, whether they were of Israel:",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 642.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Of the priests: the sons of Hobaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the sons of Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai, the Gileadite, and was named after them.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>These searched <i>among</i> their ancestral registration, but it could not be located; therefore they were considered unclean <i>and excluded</i> from the priesthood.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12486H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12486H\"></sup>The governor said to them that they should not eat from the most holy things until a priest arose with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12486I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12486I\"></sup>Urim and Thummim.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>The whole assembly together <i>was</i> 42,360,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>besides their male and their female servants, of whom <i>there were</i> 7,337; and they had 245 male and female singers.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12489J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12489J\"></sup>Their horses were 736; their mules, 245;",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup><i>their</i> camels, 435; <i>their</i> donkeys, 6,720.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>Some from among the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> gave to the work. The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12491K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12491K\"></sup>governor gave to the treasury 1,000 gold drachmas, 50 basins, 530 priests’ garments.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>Some of the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> gave into the treasury of the work 20,000 gold drachmas and 2,200 silver minas.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>That which the rest of the people gave was 20,000 gold drachmas and 2,000 silver minas and 67 priests’ garments.",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12494L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12494L\"></sup>the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people, the temple servants and all Israel, lived in their cities.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12494M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12494M\"></sup>And when the seventh month came, the sons of Israel <i>were</i> in their cities."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And all the people gathered as one man at the square which was in front of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12495A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12495A\"></sup>the Water Gate, and they asked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12495B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12495B\"></sup>Ezra the scribe to bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12495C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12495C\"></sup>the book of the law of Moses which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given to Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12496D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12496D\"></sup>Ezra the priest brought the law before the assembly of men, women and all who <i>could</i> listen with understanding, on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12496E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12496E\"></sup>the first day of the seventh month.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He read from it before the square which was in front of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12497F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12497F\"></sup>the Water Gate from early morning until midday, in the presence of men and women, those who could understand; and all the people were attentive to the book of the law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Ezra the scribe stood at a wooden podium which they had made for the purpose. And beside him stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah on his right hand; and Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hashbaddanah, Zechariah <i>and</i> Meshullam on his left hand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ezra opened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12499G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12499G\"></sup>the book in the sight of all the people for he was standing above all the people; and when he opened it, all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12499H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12499H\"></sup>stood up.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Ezra blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the great God. And all the people answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12500I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12500I\"></sup>Amen, Amen!” while lifting up their hands; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12500J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12500J\"></sup>they bowed low and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with <i>their</i> faces to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, the Levites, explained the law to the people while the people <i>remained</i> in their place.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They read from the book, from the law of God, translating to give the sense so that they understood the reading.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Nehemiah, who was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12503K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12503K\"></sup>governor, and Ezra <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12503L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12503L\"></sup>the priest <i>and</i> scribe, and the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12503M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12503M\"></sup>This day is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12503N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12503N\"></sup>do not mourn or weep.” For all the people were weeping when they heard the words of the law.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he said to them, “Go, eat of the fat, drink of the sweet, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12504O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12504O\"></sup>send portions to him who has nothing prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. Do not be grieved, for the joy of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is your strength.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the Levites calmed all the people, saying, “Be still, for the day is holy; do not be grieved.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All the people went away to eat, to drink, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12506P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12506P\"></sup>to send portions and to celebrate a great festival, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12506Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12506Q\"></sup>because they understood the words which had been made known to them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then on the second day the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of all the people, the priests and the Levites were gathered to Ezra the scribe that they might gain insight into the words of the law.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They found written in the law how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses that the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12508R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12508R\"></sup>should live in booths during the feast of the seventh month.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12509S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12509S\"></sup>So they proclaimed and circulated a proclamation in all their cities and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12509T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12509T\"></sup>in Jerusalem, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12509U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12509U\"></sup>Go out to the hills, and bring olive branches and wild olive branches, myrtle branches, palm branches and branches of <i>other</i> leafy trees, to make booths, as it is written.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the people went out and brought <i>them</i> and made booths for themselves, each <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12510V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12510V\"></sup>on his roof, and in their courts and in the courts of the house of God, and in the square at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12510W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12510W\"></sup>the Water Gate and in the square at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12510X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12510X\"></sup>the Gate of Ephraim.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The entire assembly of those who had returned from the captivity made booths and lived in them. The sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12511Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12511Y\"></sup>had indeed not done so from the days of Joshua the son of Nun to that day. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12511Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12511Z\"></sup>there was great rejoicing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12512AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12512AA\"></sup>He read from the book of the law of God daily, from the first day to the last day. And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12512AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12512AB\"></sup>celebrated the feast seven days, and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12512AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12512AC\"></sup>the eighth day <i>there was</i> a solemn assembly according to the ordinance."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now on the twenty-fourth day of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12513A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12513A\"></sup>this month the sons of Israel assembled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12513B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12513B\"></sup>with fasting, in sackcloth and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12513C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12513C\"></sup>dirt upon them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12514D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12514D\"></sup>descendants of Israel separated themselves from all foreigners, and stood and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12514E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12514E\"></sup>confessed their sins and the iniquities of their fathers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>While <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12515F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12515F\"></sup>they stood in their place, they read from the book of the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God for a fourth of the day; and for <i>another</i> fourth they confessed and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12516G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12516G\"></sup>Now on the Levites’ platform stood Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani <i>and</i> Chenani, and they cried with a loud voice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah <i>and</i> Pethahiah, said, “Arise, bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God forever and ever!O may Your glorious name be blessedAnd exalted above all blessing and praise!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12518H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12518H\"></sup>You alone are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12518I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12518I\"></sup>You have made the heavens,The heaven of heavens with all their host,The earth and all that is on it,The seas and all that is in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12518J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12518J\"></sup>You give life to all of themAnd the heavenly host bows down before You.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12519K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12519K\"></sup>Who chose AbramAnd brought him out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12519L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12519L\"></sup>Ur of the Chaldees,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12519M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12519M\"></sup>gave him the name Abraham.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“You found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12520N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12520N\"></sup>his heart faithful before You,And made a covenant with himTo give <i>him</i> the land of the Canaanite,Of the Hittite and the Amorite,Of the Perizzite, the Jebusite and the Girgashite—To give <i>it</i> to his descendants.And You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12520O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12520O\"></sup>have fulfilled Your promise,For You are righteous.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12521P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12521P\"></sup>You saw the affliction of our fathers in Egypt,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12521Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12521Q\"></sup>heard their cry by the Red Sea.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Then You performed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12522R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12522R\"></sup>signs and wonders against Pharaoh,Against all his servants and all the people of his land;For You knew that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12522S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12522S\"></sup>they acted arrogantly toward them,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12522T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12522T\"></sup>made a name for Yourself as <i>it is</i> this day.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12523U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12523U\"></sup>You divided the sea before them,So they passed through the midst of the sea on dry ground;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12523V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12523V\"></sup>their pursuers You hurled into the depths,Like a stone into raging waters.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“And with a pillar of cloud <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12524W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12524W\"></sup>You led them by day,And with a pillar of fire by nightTo light for them the wayIn which they were to go.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12525X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12525X\"></sup>You came down on Mount Sinai,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12525Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12525Y\"></sup>spoke with them from heaven;You gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12525Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12525Z\"></sup>just ordinances and true laws,Good statutes and commandments.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“So You made known to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12526AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12526AA\"></sup>Your holy sabbath,And laid down for them commandments, statutes and law,Through Your servant Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12527AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12527AB\"></sup>provided bread from heaven for them for their hunger,You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12527AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12527AC\"></sup>brought forth water from a rock for them for their thirst,And You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12527AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12527AD\"></sup>told them to enter in order to possessThe land which You swore to give them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“But they, our fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12528AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12528AE\"></sup>acted arrogantly;They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12528AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12528AF\"></sup>became stubborn and would not listen to Your commandments.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“They refused to listen,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12529AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12529AG\"></sup>did not remember Your wondrous deeds which You had performed among them;So they became stubborn and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12529AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12529AH\"></sup>appointed a leader to return to their slavery in Egypt.But You are a God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12529AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12529AI\"></sup>of forgiveness,Gracious and compassionate,Slow to anger and abounding in lovingkindness;And You did not forsake them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Even when they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12530AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12530AJ\"></sup>made for themselvesA calf of molten metalAnd said, ‘This is your GodWho brought you up from Egypt,’And committed great blasphemies,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12531AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12531AK\"></sup>You, in Your great compassion,Did not forsake them in the wilderness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12531AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12531AL\"></sup>The pillar of cloud did not leave them by day,To guide them on their way,Nor the pillar of fire by night, to light for them the way in which they were to go.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12532AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12532AM\"></sup>You gave Your good Spirit to instruct them,Your manna You did not withhold from their mouth,And You gave them water for their thirst.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12533AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12533AN\"></sup>forty years You provided for them in the wilderness <i>and</i> they were not in want;Their clothes did not wear out, nor did their feet swell.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“You also gave them kingdoms and peoples,And allotted <i>them</i> to them as a boundary.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12534AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12534AO\"></sup>They took possession of the land of Sihon the king of HeshbonAnd the land of Og the king of Bashan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“You made their sons numerous as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12535AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12535AP\"></sup>the stars of heaven,And You brought them into the landWhich You had told their fathers to enter and possess.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12536AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12536AQ\"></sup>So their sons entered and possessed the land.And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12536AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12536AR\"></sup>You subdued before them the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites,And You gave them into their hand, with their kings and the peoples of the land,To do with them as they desired.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12537AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12537AS\"></sup>They captured fortified cities and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12537AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12537AT\"></sup>fertile land.They took possession of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12537AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12537AU\"></sup>houses full of every good thing,Hewn cisterns, vineyards, olive groves,Fruit trees in abundance.So they ate, were filled and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12537AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12537AV\"></sup>grew fat,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12537AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12537AW\"></sup>reveled in Your great goodness.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12538AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12538AX\"></sup>But they became disobedient and rebelled against You,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12538AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12538AY\"></sup>cast Your law behind their backsAnd <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12538AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12538AZ\"></sup>killed Your prophets who had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12538BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12538BA\"></sup>admonished themSo that they might return to You,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12538BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12538BB\"></sup>they committed great blasphemies.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Therefore You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12539BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12539BC\"></sup>delivered them into the hand of their oppressors who oppressed them,But when they cried to You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12539BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12539BD\"></sup>in the time of their distress,You heard from heaven, and according to Your great compassionYou <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12539BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12539BE\"></sup>gave them deliverers who delivered them from the hand of their oppressors.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12540BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12540BF\"></sup>as soon as they had rest, they did evil again before You;Therefore You abandoned them to the hand of their enemies, so that they ruled over them.When they cried again to You, You heard from heaven,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12540BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12540BG\"></sup>many times You rescued them according to Your compassion,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12541BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12541BH\"></sup>admonished them in order to turn them back to Your law.Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12541BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12541BI\"></sup>they acted arrogantly and did not listen to Your commandments but sinned against Your ordinances,By <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12541BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12541BJ\"></sup>which if a man observes them he shall live.And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12541BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12541BK\"></sup>turned a stubborn shoulder and stiffened their neck, and would not listen.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12542BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12542BL\"></sup>However, You bore with them for many years,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12542BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12542BM\"></sup>admonished them by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12542BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12542BN\"></sup>Your Spirit through Your prophets,Yet they would not give ear.Therefore You gave them into the hand of the peoples of the lands.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Nevertheless, in Your great compassion You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12543BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12543BO\"></sup>did not make an end of them or forsake them,For You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12543BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12543BP\"></sup>a gracious and compassionate God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Now therefore, our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12544BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12544BQ\"></sup>the great, the mighty, and the awesome God, who keeps covenant and lovingkindness,Do not let all the hardship seem insignificant before You,Which has come upon us, our kings, our princes, our priests, our prophets, our fathers and on all Your people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12544BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12544BR\"></sup>From the days of the kings of Assyria to this day.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12545BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12545BS\"></sup>You are just in all that has come upon us;For You have dealt faithfully, but we have acted wickedly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“For our kings, our leaders, our priests and our fathers have not kept Your lawOr paid attention to Your commandments and Your admonitions with which You have admonished them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12547BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12547BT\"></sup>they, in their own kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12547BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12547BU\"></sup>With Your great goodness which You gave them,With the broad and rich land which You set before them,Did not serve You or turn from their evil deeds.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12548BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12548BV\"></sup>we are slaves today,And as to the land which You gave to our fathers to eat of its fruit and its bounty,Behold, we are slaves in it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12549BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12549BW\"></sup>Its abundant produce is for the kingsWhom You have set over us because of our sins;They also rule over our bodiesAnd over our cattle as they please,So we are in great distress.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Now because of all this<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12550BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12550BX\"></sup>We are making an agreement in writing;And on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12550BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12550BY\"></sup>sealed document <i>are the names of</i> our leaders, our Levites <i>and</i> our priests.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now on the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12551A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12551A\"></sup>sealed document <i>were the names of</i>: Nehemiah the governor, the son of Hacaliah, and Zedekiah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah. These <i>were</i> the priests.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad, Kadmiel;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>also their brothers Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hodiah, Bani, Beninu.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The leaders of the people: Parosh, Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ahiah, Hanan, Anan,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Malluch, Harim, Baanah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12578B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12578B\"></sup>the rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the temple servants and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12578C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12578C\"></sup>all those who had separated themselves from the peoples of the lands to the law of God, their wives, their sons and their daughters, all those who had knowledge and understanding,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>are joining with their kinsmen, their nobles, and are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12579D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12579D\"></sup>taking on themselves a curse and an oath to walk in God’s law, which was given through Moses, God’s servant, and to keep and to observe all the commandments of <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span> our Lord, and His ordinances and His statutes;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12580E\"></sup>that we will not give our daughters to the peoples of the land or take their daughters for our sons.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>As <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12581F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12581F\"></sup>for the peoples of the land who bring wares or any grain on the sabbath day to sell, we will not buy from them on the sabbath or a holy day; and we will forego <i>the crops</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12581G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12581G\"></sup>seventh year and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12581H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12581H\"></sup>exaction of every debt.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We also placed ourselves under obligation to contribute yearly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12582I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12582I\"></sup>one third of a shekel for the service of the house of our God:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12583J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12583J\"></sup>showbread, for the continual grain offering, for the continual burnt offering, the sabbaths, the new moon, for the appointed times, for the holy things and for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and all the work of the house of our God.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Likewise <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12584K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12584K\"></sup>we cast lots <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12584L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12584L\"></sup>for the supply of wood <i>among</i> the priests, the Levites and the people so that they might bring it to the house of our God, according to our fathers’ households, at fixed times annually, to burn on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, as it is written in the law;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and that they might bring the first fruits of our ground and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12585M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12585M\"></sup>the first fruits of all the fruit of every tree to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> annually,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12586N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12586N\"></sup>bring to the house of our God the firstborn of our sons and of our cattle, and the firstborn of our herds and our flocks as it is written in the law, for the priests who are ministering in the house of our God.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12587O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12587O\"></sup>We will also bring the first of our dough, our contributions, the fruit of every tree, the new wine and the oil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12587P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12587P\"></sup>to the priests at the chambers of the house of our God, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12587Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12587Q\"></sup>tithe of our ground to the Levites, for the Levites are they who receive the tithes in all the rural towns.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12588R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12588R\"></sup>The priest, the son of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when the Levites receive tithes, and the Levites shall bring up the tenth of the tithes to the house of our God, to the chambers of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12588S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12588S\"></sup>the storehouse.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>For the sons of Israel and the sons of Levi shall bring the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12589T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12589T\"></sup>contribution of the grain, the new wine and the oil to the chambers; there are the utensils of the sanctuary, the priests who are ministering, the gatekeepers and the singers. Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12589U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12589U\"></sup>we will not neglect the house of our God."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12590A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12590A\"></sup>the leaders of the people lived in Jerusalem, but the rest of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12590B\"></sup>cast lots to bring one out of ten to live in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12590C\"></sup>the holy city, while nine-tenths <i>remained</i> in the <i>other</i> cities.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the people blessed all the men who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12591D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12591D\"></sup>volunteered to live in Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12592E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12592E\"></sup>Now these are the heads of the provinces who lived in Jerusalem, but in the cities of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12592F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12592F\"></sup>each lived on his own property in their cities—the Israelites, the priests, the Levites, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12592G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12592G\"></sup>temple servants and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12592H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12592H\"></sup>descendants of Solomon’s servants.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some of the sons of Judah and some of the sons of Benjamin lived in Jerusalem. From the sons of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, the son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel, of the sons of Perez;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Maaseiah the son of Baruch, the son of Col-hozeh, the son of Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, the son of the Shilonite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All the sons of Perez who lived in Jerusalem were 468 able men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now these are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and after him Gabbai <i>and</i> Sallai, 928.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer, and Judah the son of Hassenuah was second in command of the city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>From the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the leader of the house of God,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and their kinsmen who performed the work of the temple, 822; and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and his kinsmen, heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, 242; and Amashsai the son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and their brothers, valiant warriors, 128. And their overseer was Zabdiel, the son of Haggedolim.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now from the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and Shabbethai and Jozabad, from the leaders of the Levites, who were in charge of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12605I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12605I\"></sup>the outside work of the house of God;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and Mattaniah the son of Mica, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, who was the leader in beginning the thanksgiving at prayer, and Bakbukiah, the second among his brethren; and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All the Levites in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12607J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12607J\"></sup>the holy city <i>were</i> 284.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Also the gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon and their brethren who kept watch at the gates, <i>were</i> 172.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The rest of Israel, of the priests <i>and</i> of the Levites, <i>were</i> in all the cities of Judah, each <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12609K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12609K\"></sup>on his own inheritance.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12610L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12610L\"></sup>the temple servants were living in Ophel, and Ziha and Gishpa were in charge of the temple servants.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12611M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12611M\"></sup>the overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Mica, from the sons of Asaph, who were the singers for the service of the house of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12612N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12612N\"></sup>For <i>there was</i> a commandment from the king concerning them and a firm regulation for the song leaders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12612O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12612O\"></sup>day by day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12613P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12613P\"></sup>of Zerah the son of Judah, was the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12613Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12613Q\"></sup>king’s representative in all matters concerning the people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now as for the villages with their fields, some of the sons of Judah lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12614R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12614R\"></sup>Kiriath-arba and its towns, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12614S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12614S\"></sup>Dibon and its towns, and in Jekabzeel and its villages,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and in Jeshua, in Moladah and Beth-pelet,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and in Hazar-shual, in Beersheba and its towns,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and in Ziklag, in Meconah and in its towns,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and in En-rimmon, in Zorah and in Jarmuth,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages, Lachish and its fields, Azekah and its towns. So they encamped from Beersheba as far as the valley of Hinnom.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The sons of Benjamin also <i>lived</i> from Geba <i>onward</i>, at Michmash and Aija, at Bethel and its towns,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>at Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Lod and Ono, the valley of craftsmen.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>From the Levites, <i>some</i> divisions in Judah belonged to Benjamin."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Now these are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12626A\"></sup>the priests and the Levites who came up with Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Shemaiah and Joiarib, Jedaiah,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah and Jedaiah. These were the heads of the priests and their kinsmen in the days of Jeshua.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Levites <i>were</i> Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, <i>and</i> Mattaniah <i>who was</i> in charge of the songs of thanksgiving, he and his brothers.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brothers, stood opposite them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12634B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12634B\"></sup>in <i>their</i> service divisions.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jeshua became the father of Joiakim, and Joiakim became the father of Eliashib, and Eliashib became the father of Joiada,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Joiada became the father of Jonathan, and Jonathan became the father of Jaddua.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now in the days of Joiakim, the priests, the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> were: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>of Malluchi, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethanel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>As for the Levites, the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> were registered in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, and Johanan and Jaddua; so <i>were</i> the priests in the reign of Darius the Persian.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Levi, the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, were registered in the Book of the Chronicles up to the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The heads of the Levites <i>were</i> Hashabiah, Sherebiah and Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brothers opposite them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12649C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12649C\"></sup>to praise <i>and</i> give thanks, as prescribed by David the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12649D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12649D\"></sup>division corresponding to division.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon <i>and</i> Akkub <i>were</i> gatekeepers keeping watch at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12650E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12650E\"></sup>the storehouses of the gates.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>These <i>served</i> in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12651F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12651F\"></sup>Nehemiah the governor and of Ezra the priest <i>and</i> scribe.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought out the Levites from all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem so that they might celebrate the dedication with gladness, with hymns of thanksgiving and with songs <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12652G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12652G\"></sup><i>to the accompaniment</i> of cymbals, harps and lyres.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the sons of the singers were assembled from the district around Jerusalem, and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12653H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12653H\"></sup>the villages of the Netophathites,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>from Beth-gilgal and from <i>their</i> fields in Geba and Azmaveth, for the singers had built themselves villages around Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The priests and the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12655I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12655I\"></sup>purified themselves; they also purified the people, the gates and the wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then I had the leaders of Judah come up on top of the wall, and I appointed two great choirs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12656J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12656J\"></sup>the first proceeding to the right on top of the wall toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12656K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12656K\"></sup>the Refuse Gate.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah followed them,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>with Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, Jeremiah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and some of the sons of the priests with trumpets; <i>and</i> Zechariah the son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micaiah, the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his kinsmen, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, Judah <i>and</i> Hanani, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12661L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12661L\"></sup>with the musical instruments of David the man of God. And Ezra the scribe went before them.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>At <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12662M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12662M\"></sup>the Fountain Gate they went directly up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12662N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12662N\"></sup>the steps of the city of David by the stairway of the wall above the house of David to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12662O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12662O\"></sup>the Water Gate on the east.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12663P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12663P\"></sup>The second choir proceeded to the left, while I followed them with half of the people on the wall, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12663Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12663Q\"></sup>above the Tower of Furnaces, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12663R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12663R\"></sup>the Broad Wall,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12664S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12664S\"></sup>the Gate of Ephraim, by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12664T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12664T\"></sup>the Old Gate, by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12664U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12664U\"></sup>Fish Gate, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12664V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12664V\"></sup>the Tower of Hananel and the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Sheep Gate; and they stopped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12664W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12664W\"></sup>the Gate of the Guard.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then the two choirs took their stand in the house of God. So did I and half of the officials with me;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>and the priests, Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah and Hananiah, with the trumpets;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam and Ezer. And the singers sang, with Jezrahiah <i>their</i> leader,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and on that day they offered great sacrifices and rejoiced because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12668X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12668X\"></sup>God had given them great joy, even the women and children rejoiced, so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard from afar.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>On that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12669Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12669Y\"></sup>men were also appointed over the chambers for the stores, the contributions, the first fruits and the tithes, to gather into them from the fields of the cities the portions required by the law for the priests and Levites; for Judah rejoiced over the priests and Levites who served.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>For they performed the worship of their God and the service of purification, together with the singers and the gatekeepers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12670Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12670Z\"></sup>in accordance with the command of David <i>and</i> of his son Solomon.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>For in the days of David and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12671AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12671AA\"></sup>Asaph, in ancient times, <i>there were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12671AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12671AB\"></sup>leaders of the singers, songs of praise and hymns of thanksgiving to God.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>So all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel and Nehemiah gave the portions due the singers and the gatekeepers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12672AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12672AC\"></sup>as each day required, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12672AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12672AD\"></sup>set apart the consecrated <i>portion</i> for the Levites, and the Levites set apart the consecrated <i>portion</i> for the sons of Aaron."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>On that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12673A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12673A\"></sup>they read aloud from the book of Moses in the hearing of the people; and there was found written in it that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12673B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12673B\"></sup>no Ammonite or Moabite should ever enter the assembly of God,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>because they did not meet the sons of Israel with bread and water, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12674C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12674C\"></sup>hired Balaam against them to curse them. However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12674D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12674D\"></sup>our God turned the curse into a blessing.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So when they heard the law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12675E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12675E\"></sup>they excluded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12675F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12675F\"></sup>all foreigners from Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now prior to this, Eliashib the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12676G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12676G\"></sup>who was appointed over the chambers of the house of our God, being related to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12676H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12676H\"></sup>Tobiah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>had prepared a large room for him, where formerly they put the grain offerings, the frankincense, the utensils and the tithes of grain, wine and oil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12677I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12677I\"></sup>prescribed for the Levites, the singers and the gatekeepers, and the contributions for the priests.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But during all this <i>time</i> I was not in Jerusalem, for in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12678J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12678J\"></sup>the thirty-second year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12678K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12678K\"></sup>Artaxerxes king of Babylon I had gone to the king. After some time, however, I asked leave from the king,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and I came to Jerusalem and learned about the evil that Eliashib had done for Tobiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12679L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12679L\"></sup>by preparing a room for him in the courts of the house of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It was very displeasing to me, so I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12680M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12680M\"></sup>threw all of Tobiah’s household goods out of the room.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I gave an order and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12681N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12681N\"></sup>they cleansed the rooms; and I returned there the utensils of the house of God with the grain offerings and the frankincense.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I also discovered that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12682O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12682O\"></sup>the portions of the Levites had not been given <i>them</i>, so that the Levites and the singers who performed the service had gone away, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12682P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12682P\"></sup>each to his own field.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12683Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12683Q\"></sup>reprimanded the officials and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12683R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12683R\"></sup>Why is the house of God forsaken?” Then I gathered them together and restored them to their posts.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All Judah then brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12684S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12684S\"></sup>the tithe of the grain, wine and oil into the storehouses.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>In charge of the storehouses I appointed Shelemiah the priest, Zadok the scribe, and Pedaiah of the Levites, and in addition to them was Hanan the son of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12685T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12685T\"></sup>they were considered reliable, and it was their task to distribute to their kinsmen.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12686U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12686U\"></sup>Remember me for this, O my God, and do not blot out my loyal deeds which I have performed for the house of my God and its services.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In those days I saw in Judah some who were treading wine presses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12687V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12687V\"></sup>on the sabbath, and bringing in sacks of grain and loading <i>them</i> on donkeys, as well as wine, grapes, figs and all kinds of loads, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12687W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12687W\"></sup>and they brought <i>them</i> into Jerusalem on the sabbath day. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12687X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12687X\"></sup>I admonished <i>them</i> on the day they sold food.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Also men of Tyre were living there <i>who</i> imported fish and all kinds of merchandise, and sold <i>them</i> to the sons of Judah on the sabbath, even in Jerusalem.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12689Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12689Y\"></sup>I reprimanded the nobles of Judah and said to them, “What is this evil thing you are doing, by profaning the sabbath day?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12690Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12690Z\"></sup>Did not your fathers do the same, so that our God brought on us and on this city all this trouble? Yet you are adding to the wrath on Israel by profaning the sabbath.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12691AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12691AA\"></sup>It came about that just as it grew dark at the gates of Jerusalem before the sabbath, I commanded that the doors should be shut and that they should not open them until after the sabbath. Then I stationed some of my servants at the gates <i>so that</i> no load would enter on the sabbath day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Once or twice the traders and merchants of every kind of merchandise spent the night outside Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12693AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12693AB\"></sup>I warned them and said to them, “Why do you spend the night in front of the wall? If you do so again, I will use force against you.” From that time on they did not come on the sabbath.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And I commanded the Levites that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12694AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12694AC\"></sup>they should purify themselves and come as gatekeepers to sanctify the sabbath day. <i>For</i> this also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12694AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12694AD\"></sup>remember me, O my God, and have compassion on me according to the greatness of Your lovingkindness.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In those days I also saw that the Jews had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12695AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12695AE\"></sup>married women from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12695AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12695AF\"></sup>Ashdod, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12695AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12695AG\"></sup>Ammon <i>and</i> Moab.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As for their children, half spoke in the language of Ashdod, and none of them was able to speak the language of Judah, but the language of his own people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12697AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12697AH\"></sup>I contended with them and cursed them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12697AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12697AI\"></sup>struck some of them and pulled out their hair, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12697AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12697AJ\"></sup>made them swear by God, “You shall not give your daughters to their sons, nor take of their daughters for your sons or for yourselves.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12698AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12698AK\"></sup>Did not Solomon king of Israel sin regarding these things? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12698AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12698AL\"></sup>Yet among the many nations there was no king like him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12698AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12698AM\"></sup>he was loved by his God, and God made him king over all Israel; nevertheless the foreign women caused even him to sin.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Do we then hear about you that you have committed all this great evil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12699AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12699AN\"></sup>by acting unfaithfully against our God by marrying foreign women?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Even one of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was a son-in-law of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12700AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12700AO\"></sup>Sanballat the Horonite, so I drove him away from me.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12701AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12701AP\"></sup>Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12701AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12701AQ\"></sup>covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12702AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12702AR\"></sup>Thus I purified them from everything foreign and appointed duties for the priests and the Levites, each in his task,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and <i>I arranged</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12703AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12703AS\"></sup>for the supply of wood at appointed times and for the first fruits. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12703AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12703AT\"></sup>Remember me, O my God, for good."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;